FBIS4-19570 "drweu076_o_94006" FBIS-WEU-94-076 Daily Report 20 Apr 1994 CYPRUS U.S. Official Doubtful on Agreement by Deadline U.S. Official Doubtful on Agreement by Deadline NC2004113594 Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio Network in Greek 1030 GMT 20 Apr 94 NC2004113594 Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio Network Greek BFN [Text] The United States maintains its hopes that progress can be achieved on the confidence-building measures, but doubts whether this progress can be achieved by the end of April, as stipulated in the latest report from UN Secretary General Butrus Butrus-Ghali and the Security Council's letter to the secretary general. This position was expressed by a U.S. official to a CyBC [Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation] correspondent in New York. In the meantime, Robert Lamb, the U.S. State Department's special coordinator on Cyprus, will meet Saturday [23 April] with Joe Clark, the UN secretary general's special representative in Cyprus, to review the proximity talks on the confidence-building measures. The meeting will take place in view of Clark's visit to Nicosia next week.
